==English==

===Phrase===
'''[[once]] [[or]] [[twice]]'''

# {{idiom}} A small, indefinite [[number]] of [[time]]s.
#:''Have you changed a tyre before? &mdash; Yes, '''once or twice'''.''

===Usage notes===
This is most often used figuratively, to mean "[[many]], many times."

